<div type="definition">

    <p resp="#CH" modified="2020-11-06T21:34:04.247+09:00">IMPORTANT ENDURING PROPERTY. </p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[ELEVATED/INFORMAL]</p>
<p>[LASTING/TEMPORARY]</p>
<p>[LITERAL/TRANSFERRED]</p>
<p>1. Yè 業 refers to typically permanent assets of significant proportions.</p>
<p>[ELEVATED?], [LASTING]</p>
<p>2. Chǎn 產 refers to considerable but not necessarily inalienable assets, typically not viewed as entirely inherited.</p>
<p>[LITERAL]</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>產業</p>
<p>產</p>
<p>業</p>
<p>財產</p>
<p>資產</p>
